  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>

    <refpurpose>Examine &i2c; registers</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command>
      <arg choice=req><replaceable>i2cbus</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice=req><replaceable>address</replaceable></arg>
      <arg><replaceable>mode</replaceable></arg>
      <arg><replaceable>bank</replaceable>
	<arg><replaceable>bankreg</replaceable></arg>
      </arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para>&dhpackage; is a small helper program to examine registers
      visible through the &i2c; bus.  
    </para>

  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>
    
    <para>At least two options must be provided to &dhpackage;.
      <replaceable>i2cbus</replaceable> indicates the number of the
      &i2c; bus to be scanned.  This number should correspond to one
      of the busses listed in <filename>/proc/bus/i2c</filename>.
      <replaceable>address</replaceable> indicates the address to be
      scanned on that bus, and is an integer between 0 and 127.  The
      <replaceable>mode</replaceable> parameter, if specified, is one
      of the letters <literal>b</literal>, <literal>w</literal>,
      <literal>s</literal>, or <literal>i</literal>, corresponding to
      a read size of a single byte, a 16-bit word, an SMBus block, or
      an &i2c; block, respectively.  If the
      <replaceable>mode</replaceable> parameter is omitted,
      &dhpackage; defaults to byte access.</para>

    <para>The <replaceable>bank</replaceable> and
      <replaceable>bankaddr</replaceable> parameters appear to only be
      useful on W83781 chips.  <replaceable>bank</replaceable> is an
      integer between 0 and 15, and <replaceable>bankreg</replaceable>
      is an integer between 0 and 255.  The W83781 data sheet has more
      information on the usage of these parameters.</para>

  </refsect1>
